<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#123#000055#    248.26#">Va. Code Ann. § 55-248.26</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_55-248.26"/><heading><desig>§ 55-248.26.</desig><title>Tenant's remedies for landlord's unlawful ouster, exclusion or diminution of service</title></heading><bodyText><p>If the landlord unlawfully removes or excludes the tenant from the premises or willfully diminishes services to the tenant by interrupting or causing the interruption of gas, water, or other essential service to the tenant, the tenant may obtain an order from a general district court to recover possession, require the landlord to resume any such interrupted utility service, or terminate the rental agreement and, in any case, recover the actual damages sustained by him and a reasonable attorney fee. If the rental agreement is terminated the landlord shall return all of the security deposit in accordance with <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 55-248.15:1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 55 -248.15:1">§ 55-248.15:1.<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#142#        55#    248.15#         1#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation></p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>1974, c. 680; <citation normalizedCite="2000 VA CH 760"><content><span normalizedCite="2000 Va. Ch. 760">2000, c. 760<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/>